the problem is about when we need a pipeline or a chainOfResponsibility of objs
for processing a request (order is matter)

imagine we have a web server, and we need to deal with the concept of
an HTTP request.
we have to do some steps in order like
at first authenticate,
then logging,
then compression (compress the response like JSON,HTML file to reduce size))

if we do all of these on WebServer class we violate Single Responsibility concept
so we create separate class for each of them (Authenticator, Compressor, Logger)
and use them on WebServer class.

problem: WebServer is coupled to these classes now
         we can use interface and inject the dependency to decouple them
         but the order of these step will be remained hard coded on WebServer!
         if in future we want to disable logging for a scenario
         we have to change WebServer class

         if we want to add a new step we need to change WebServer class!
         violate open close principle!
